2026-04-21 02:46:30 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['cube_ctrl6_switch'] hypothesis_explanation='All control module indicator LEDs are missing, which would open the parallel indicator paths but does not interrupt the main current path to the lamp when the switches are closed. Bypassing any control module other than cube_ctrl6 causes the lamp to turn on, but with cube_ctrl6 in place, even with all switches closed, the lamp remains off. The cables themselves have electrical continuity when bypassed, so the fault likely resides within cube_ctrl6. Since replacement of the entire cube_ctrl6 module did not repair the fault, this suggests a specific internal fault: the switch inside cube_ctrl6 is likely open (faulty), preventing current from passing through even when the switch appears closed. The switch is the only element in the series path that could cause a break with the LEDs absent and working cables.'
