name: Test -> Control module switch and bypass circuit,
description: With the system powered, temporarily bypass one control module by connecting its input and output cables directly (effectively removing it from the circuit), then observe if either the load indicator or main lamp turns on. Repeat for each control module, one at a time., outcome='When each control module was tested individually in the circuit, the lamp turned ON for all modules except cube_ctrl6, where it remained OFF. Visual inspections show that both the main load lamp and the internal indicator lamp are not lit in the system’s current configuration and have no observable internal faults. No polarity inversions were detected in these steps.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=2725.0, cost_breakdown=[('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_peephole', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load', 320.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> cube_ctrl6 associated cables/connectors,
description: Test continuity of both cables going into and out of control module 6 by temporarily connecting the input and output cables (bypassing the cube entirely) and ensuring the corresponding connectors are making electrical connection when re-connected to the module. Observe if lamp operates correctly with the bypass still in place and connections wiggled/reseated., outcome='Both the positive and negative input and output cables for control module 6 were successfully bridged with low resistance, confirming electrical continuity via bypass. The lamp operated correctly with the bypass in place, and no observable faults were noted in the lamp. Continuity checks via multimeter could not be performed due to tool unavailability.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=110.0, cost_breakdown=[('short_ports', 20.0), ('short_ports', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
